## 6.7 Cisco Packet Tracer

### What Is It?
- Free network simulation tool by Cisco
- Create virtual networks with routers, switches, PCs
- Configure protocols without real hardware
- Download from [netacad.com](https://www.netacad.com)

### Essential Exercises

| Exercise | What You Learn |
|----------|---------------|
| Create a basic LAN with 4 PCs and a switch | Switching, MAC addresses |
| Connect two LANs with a router | Routing, IP addressing |
| Configure DHCP server | DHCP DORA process |
| Set up VLANs on a switch | VLAN segmentation |
| Configure static routing between 3 routers | Routing tables |
| Configure OSPF on a multi-router network | Dynamic routing |
| Set up ACLs (Access Control Lists) | Firewall basics |
| Build a DNS server | DNS resolution |
| Configure NAT/PAT | Address translation |
| Create a full enterprise network | Integration of all concepts |

### Other Simulation Tools
- **GNS3** — Advanced, uses real Cisco IOS images
- **EVE-NG** — Enterprise-grade network emulator
- **Mininet** — SDN (Software Defined Networking) simulator
- **NS-3** — Academic network simulator for research
